Package com.taco.tacository.util.tools.list_tools

Interface OperationListener<E>

Type Parameters:
E - The type of element in the ObservableList this OperationListener is listening to.
All Known Subinterfaces:
ListTools.OperationResponder<E>, ListTools.SimpleOperationListener<E>, ListTools.SimpleOperationResponder<E>, ListTools.UnlinkedOperationResponder<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
OperationHandler
public interface OperationListener<E>

An interface used to help streamline ListChangeListener events to be more easily understandable.

Details

The primary usage pattern for OperationListener is as follows:

  1. The primary implementation of OperationListener is the OperationHandler class.
  2. OperationListeners are used as the input to OperationHandler static factory methods located in ListTools
    • Root Factory Method: ListTools.applyListener(... OperationListener)
  3. Various interface extensions of OperationListener exist to allow varying amounts and types of lambda factory input parameters.

Operation Event Response Functions

See individual method documentation for additional information.

Permutation

  1. On Pre-Permutate: Executed immediately prior to triggering all permutation operations that occurred in a single Change Event step.
  2. On Post-Permutate: Executed immediately after triggering all permutation operations that occurred in a single Change Event step.
  3. On Permutate: Executed for each permutation operation that occurred in a single Change Event step.

Addition

  1. On Pre-Add: Executed immediately prior to triggering all addition operations that occurred in a single Change Event step.
  2. On Post-Add: Executed immediately after triggering all addition operations that occurred in a single Change Event step.
  3. On Add: Executed for each addition operation that occurred in a single Change Event step.

Removal

  1. On Pre-Remove: Executed immediately prior to triggering all removal operations that occurred in a single Change Event step.
  2. On Post-Remove: Executed immediately after triggering all removal operations that occurred in a single Change Event step.
  3. On Remove: Executed for each removal operation that occurred in a single Change Event step.
